level_3.body_template:
To,
The Grievance Officer
{platform_legal_name}
{platform_address}

Subject: Formal Grievance Under Consumer Protection Act, 2019 and E-Commerce Rules, 2020

Dear Sir/Madam,

I am writing to formally escalate a consumer grievance that remains unresolved despite multiple attempts at resolution through your customer support channels.

COMPLAINT DETAILS:
- Order ID: {order_id}
- Product: {item_name}
- Category: {category}
- Amount Paid: ₹{amount}
- Order Date: {order_date}
- Delivery Date: {delivery_date}
- Issue: {issue_description}

TIMELINE OF COMPLAINT:
{complaint_timeline}

Despite the above communications, my complaint remains unresolved. This constitutes a deficiency in service under Section 2(6) of the Consumer Protection Act, 2019.

Furthermore, as per the Consumer Protection (E-Commerce) Rules, 2020:
- Rule 4(4): Every e-commerce entity shall establish an adequate grievance redressal mechanism
- Rule 4(5): The grievance officer shall acknowledge receipt of consumer complaint within 48 hours and resolve it within one month

I hereby demand:
1. Immediate {return_type} of ₹{amount}
2. Compensation for the mental agony and inconvenience caused
3. Written acknowledgment of this grievance within 48 hours as mandated by law

If this matter is not resolved within 15 days of receipt of this communication, I shall be compelled to file a formal complaint with:
- National Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission (NCDRC)
- Central Consumer Protection Authority (CCPA)
- Department of Consumer Affairs

{evidence_section}

Regards,
{user_name}
{user_address}
Email: {user_email}
Phone: {user_phone}
Date: {current_date}
